The President and Senior Administration officials met with members of the Congressional Hispanic Caucus to discuss the need to fix the broken immigration system. The President expressed disappointment that the DREAM Act failed to pass and that Congressional action on immigration reform has stalled. The CHC members asked the President to consider administrative options, but he emphasized that legislative action is necessary to fix the system. The President outlined the Administration's efforts to improve the legal immigration system, secure borders, and enhance immigration enforcement. He also updated the CHC members on recent meetings with stakeholders from various sectors and parties to elevate the immigration debate. The President and CHC members agreed on the importance of legislative action to address the broken immigration system.